weeks stack (62°14′s 59°3′w﻿ / ﻿62.233°s 59.050°w) is a sea stack lying off the north tip of nelson island in the northern approach to fildes strait, in the south shetland islands. named by the united kingdom antarctic place-names committee (uk-apc) in 1961 for captain weeks, master of the british sealing vessel horatio from london, who visited the south shetland islands in 1820-21.